Service Cloud

Share Articles in Channels in Lightning Knowledge

You can share the contents of an article in an email, Social Post, Chat, or Messaging conversation. Close cases by inserting article summaries or text snippets in case interactions across channels.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience and all editions with Knowledge except Essentials.
Salesforce Knowledge is available for an additional cost in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To share article contents in the case feed:
Edit on cases
Read on knowledge articles

To share internal articles in the case feed:
Allow user to share internal knowledge articles externally

You must have the Knowledge component available in your Lightning page. Your org must have relevant channels set up, such as email, social, or chat.

From the Knowledge component or articles related list, select one of these actions:

Insert Article into Social Post
Insert Article into Email
Insert Article into Conversation
Click Insert.

For Email and Social Post, if an article wasn't attached to a case, these actions add it to the caseâ€™s related list.
title: Sharing Knowledge Articles in Service Cloud
